bug.short_desc: Graphic assets for Join Mozilla promo in Mozilla & You newsletter

long_desc.thetext:
Hey Tara,
We need a graphic for the Join Mozilla story in the upcoming Mozilla & You newsletter. There aren't a lot of options for what we could use (the crest would be ideal, but I'm not sure if that's back in play or not):
1) The heart graphic from the Join Mozilla landing page that Lee is using for the mozilla.org promo 2) The T-shirt or card image
I'll check in on the crest stuff.
In terms of image size, Winston has told me that they need to be high res, bigger than 100x100.
We need this by mid-next week if that's possible.
Let me know if you have any additional questions and thanks!

Thanks Chelsea.
Let me know about the crest, that's pretty key :)
Otherwise, we can produce a graphic similar to what we've done before:
* Extracting a piece of the scene (with the heart sign) into a small promo * Did you want this to have no text? possible text could be "join mozilla". Otherwise, it might work best to keep the graphic simple and image-only. * In terms of aspect ration, can you give me exact dimensions please? * In terms of time, something by April 13th sounds good?

I will let you know as soon as I can.
As for the dimensions, Winston gave me the direction that it only needed to be high res. Winston, can you give Tara/Lee a little more detail for his?
April 13 is great, I think. Winston, can you confirm that it gives you enough time? Thanks

Hey Winston, Is there a chance you could send me a screenshot of the newsletter with reference to where this promo would sit? It always helps to design w/ the context in mind. Also, in terms of a "hi-res" image - are you requesting the image source file, or the image in 300dpi (print resolution)? Just wanted to clarify, as the web/newsletter resolution only needs to be 72dpi. Apologies if I missed something!

Created attachment 524330 new email format
Hey Lee - 72 dpi will be great.
Check out the attached. It will go in place of what you see in Firefox tales.

Created attachment 524425 join mozilla promo 100x100
Thanks for the ref file, Winston. Here's a quicky png w/ JOIN MOZILLA in it. Chelsea, let me know if this works. Thanks!
Hey Lee I think that's totally the right idea. Can we soften or round the edges a little bit on it?
I think the "frame" of the promo block already has a soft / rounded edge. And this would just be inserted in it. In which case, we should be OK. Chelsea do you agree?
I'm pretty sure that rounded border is set in the code. The 100x100px is the hard edged square.
That's what I thought too. In that case, Are we good to close this ?

Created attachment 524440 newsletter mockup FPO
Here's the JOIN promo in context of the email (under Firefox Tales) with the rounded borders. The copy is obviously wrong for Join, but you can see what the promo will look like w/ that border treatment.

Hey Lee,
Can you tone down the red a bit? Maybe use some of the red in from the Mozilla.org promos? It's too stark right now.
Thanks!

Created attachment 524745 join mozilla promo 100x100
Hey Chelsea, I'm using the same red as all the other Join Mozilla graphics. I think this will work better now (and seem less stark) that I filled the top right quadrant w/ more of the angry -er, happy mob!

Agree with Lee that we should keep the colors consistent. It's a pretty tiny space to design for... especially since we have the "Join Mozilla" consuming a lot of space. The only thing I an suggest is to reduce the "crowd" graphic and have it feel more like a texture, than focusing in on the individual people.
I also think that this looks pretty good overall and if you're happy with it (Chelsea) then we can not overthink and wrap it up :) Let us know how you feel.
Hey Chelsea, can you please do a quick review and let us know if we can close this bug out? Thanks.
